	 Two nabbed for trying to extort J Lo over wedding video 
	 Two men, one of whom is a convicted murderer, have been arrested for stealing a video of Jennifer Lopez and her husband Marc Anthony's wedding and trying to obtain US$1 million for its safe return. The duo is now facing charges of conspiracy, attempted grand larceny and possession of stolen property. 
